data.title: Night Sky Map & Planets Visible Tonight in Heber City
data.meta_description: Sky map showing night sky tonight in Heber City, Utah, USA. What planets are visible? Where is Mars, Saturn or Venus? What is the bright star in the sky?
data.text:
Venus rise and set in Heber City

Try after sunset.

Venus sets shortly after sunset, so it is very close to the horizon. This makes it very difficult to observe. Venus is visible by day, but may be hard to find.

Mars rise and set in Heber City

View before sunrise.

Mars can best be seen in the hours just before sunrise. Visibility deteriorates as the sky gets brighter.

Jupiter rise and set in Heber City

View before sunrise.

Jupiter can best be seen in the hours just before sunrise. Visibility deteriorates as the sky gets brighter.

Saturn rise and set in Heber City

Most of the night until sunrise.

Saturn is visible during most of the night, but it is best viewed in the early morning hours and until sunrise.

Uranus rise and set in Heber City

View before sunrise. Bring binoculars.

Uranus can best be seen in the hours just before sunrise. Visibility deteriorates as the sky gets brighter. You may need binoculars.

Neptune rise and set in Heber City

Most of the night until sunrise. Use binoculars.

Neptune is visible during most of the night, but it is best viewed in the early morning hours and until sunrise. Very faint, use binoculars.
